    <body>

        <div xml:id="Kali49-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">itu nīr ivvāṟu varukiṉṟa varavu emakkut tuṉpattiṟkuk kāraṇamākā niṉṟateṉak 
            kūṟi iravu varuvāṉait tōḻi pakal varukaveṉṟatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali49">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>koṭuvari tākki veṉṟa varuttamoṭu</l>
                <l>neṭuvarai maruṅkiṟ ṟuñcum yāṉai</l>
                <l>naṉaviṟṟāṉ ceytatu maṉatta tākaliṟ</l>
                <l>kaṉaviṟ kaṇṭu katumeṉa verīip</l>
                <l>putuva tāka malarnta vēṅkaiyai</l>
                <l>yatuveṉa vuṇarntata ṉaṇinala murukkip</l>
                <l>pēṇā muṉpiṟṟaṉ ciṉantaṇin tammaraṅ</l>
                <l>kāṇum poḻuti ṉōkkal cellātu</l>
                <l>nāṇi yiṟaiñcu naṉmalai naṉṉāṭa;</l>
                <l rend="space">pōteḻiṉ malaruṇka ṇivaṇmāṭṭu nīyiṉṉa</l>
                <l>kātalai yeṉpatō viṉitumaṟ ṟiṉṉātē</l>
                <l>miṉṉōruṅ kaṇṇāka viṭiyeṉṉāy peyaleṉṉā</l>
                <l>yiṉṉatō rāriṭai yīṅkunī varuvatai;</l>
                <l rend="space">iṉpuṟa vaḷittaṉai yivaṇmāṭṭu nīyiṉṉa</l>
                <l>vaṉpiṉai yeṉpatō viṉitumaṟ ṟiṉṉātē</l>
                <l>maṇaṅkamaḻ mārpiṉai mañciva raṭukkampōḻn</l>
                <l>taṇaṅkuṭai yāriṭai yīṅkunī varuvatai;</l>
                <l rend="space">iruḷuṟa ḻiruṅkūnta livaṇmāṭṭu nīyiṉṉa</l>
                <l>varuḷiṉai yeṉpatō viṉitumaṟ ṟiṉṉātē</l>
                <l>oḷiṟuvēl valaṉēnti yoruvaṉyā ṉeṉṉātu</l>
                <l>kaḷiṟiyaṅ kāriṭai yīṅkunī varuvatai;</l>
                <l rend="space">ataṉāl,</l>
                <l>iraviṉ vāra laiya viravuvī</l>
                <l>yakalaṟai varikkuñ cāraṟ</l>
                <l>pakalum peṟuvaiyiva ṭaṭameṉ ṟōḷē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="9cd">            O man from the good land of good mountains, </l>
<l corresp="2">where the elephant that sleeps at the side of the tall mountain </l>
<l corresp="1">with suffering, as it had been attacked [and] vanquished by a [tiger with] curved stripes, </l>
<l corresp="3">because what is has done in reality is in [its] mind, </l>
<l corresp="4">suddenly being frightened when seeing [that] in [its] dream </l>
<l>[and] ruining the ornate beauty of the kino tree </l>
<l corresp="5f">that newly blossoms, which it has perceived as that [tiger],</l>
<l>at the time it sees that tree after its anger about [its] dishonored strength</l>
<l corresp="7f">has calmed down cannot look at [it]</l>
<l corresp="8ab">[and] bows down in shame, </l>
<l rend="space">As for saying that you have such love for her with kajal eyes</l>
<l>[like] budding graceful blossoms, it is sweet. Unsweet is</l>
<l>your coming here by the difficult road that is like this,</l>
<l>while it is a place that listens to lightning, not saying “thunder”, not saying “rain”.</l>
<l rend="space">As for saying that you have such love for her, being one </l>
<l>who provided pleasantly, it is sweet. Unsweet is</l>
<l>your coming here by the frightful difficult road,</l>
<l>crossing the cloud-climbed slope, you with [your] chest fragrant of scent.</l>
<l rend="space">As for saying that you have such consideration for her with dark tresses</l>
<l>that resemble the darkness, it is sweet. Unsweet is</l>
<l>your coming here by the difficult road where elephant bulls stir</l>
<l>without saying I am [only] one man, holding up [your] shining spear in victory.</l>
<l rend="space">Therefore,</l>
<l>don’t come at night, lord. On [your] slope</l>
<l>where the wide rocks are lined with mixed flowers</l>
<l>you will obtain [them] also by day, her broad soft shoulders.</l>
            </lg>
